<br>
Under this strategy (I would call it the &quot;Slam Bam FM&quot; strategy...hehehe), a healer/caster will give a tell/ooc/shout to his/her dueling (tank) partner as soon as OOM. The tanks who will do this job can be assigned prior to the raid...each dueling tank will be assigned to maybe 1-3 healers/casters. Preferrably, the designated tanks for these duels would be those who are higher levels so that they can kill their dueling partners fast.<br>
<br>
I believe that this strategy will help to reduce exp lost for those healers/nukers. Besides, there will also be less rezzes to be done once the raid is over.<br>
<br>
However, there are two problems that I can see with having this strategy in place. First, there will always be a chance of the tank to miss the healer's/nuker's message to start dueling. Second, it will probably a little bit confusing on which corpses that need to be rezzed if the corpses of those who got killed by the dragon or other mobs are mixed with those who died because of duels. The second problem can almost be eliminated though if we designate an area as a dueling area.<br>
<br>
Anyway, that's just my 2cp. I hope it is something that might help the raid. Thanks.<br>
<br>
